<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871202-0126 </DOCNO><HL> General Electric Co.Wins Army ContractFor Helicopter Job</HL><DD> 12/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GE ML LK MDAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Electric Co. received an $805.8 million Army contract to produce engines for 80 Blackhawk helicopters by the end of 1989.    As part of the overall contract, the Army awarded the company $21.5 million as the first payment for the engine work. The Blackhawk is the Army's main troop-transport helicopter.    In addition, the Navy awarded GE a $10 million contract to modify an infrared tracking system the company is already building for the F-14 fighter jet.    In other contracts issued yesterday, Martin Marietta Corp. got a $60.2 million Army award for Pershing missile-engineering services.    Units of Lockheed Corp. were given contracts totaling $34.7 million for S-3A aircraft improvements for the Navy and aircraft-engineering services for the Air Force.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. won a $21 million Navy contract for EF-18A aircraft production for Spain.    Gulfstream Aerospace Corp. received a $10.5 million Air Force contract for C-20 aircraft support. </TEXT></DOC>